7 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
8 // ----
9 // This implements bottom-up and top-down register pressure reduction list ----
10 // schedulers, using standard algorithms. The basic approach uses a priority ----
11 // queue of available nodes to schedule. One at a time, nodes are taken from ----
12 // the priority queue (thus in priority order), checked for legality to ----
13 // schedule, and emitted if legal. ----
14 // ----
15 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
16 ----

307 /// GetCostForDef - Looks up the register class and cost for a given definition. ----

323 ----
324 // Special handling for CopyFromReg of untyped values. ----

327 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = MF.getRegInfo().getRegClass(Reg); 0

329 Cost = 1; 0

331 } ----
332 ----

339 return; 0
340 } ----
341 ----

344 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = TII->getRegClass(Desc, Idx, TRI, MF); 0
345 assert(RC && "Not a valid register class"); 0
346 RegClass = RC->getID(); 0
347 // FIXME: Cost arbitrarily set to 1 because there doesn't seem to be a ----
348 // better way to determine it. ----
349 Cost = 1; 0
350 } else { ----

352 Cost = TLI->getRepRegClassCostFor(VT); 0

441 /// IsChainDependent - Test if Outer is reachable from Inner through ----
442 /// chain dependencies. ----
443 static bool IsChainDependent(SDNode *Outer, SDNode *Inner, 0
444 unsigned NestLevel, ----
445 const TargetInstrInfo *TII) { ----
446 SDNode *N = Outer; 0
447 while (true) { ----
448 if (N == Inner) 0
449 return true; 0
450 // For a TokenFactor, examine each operand. There may be multiple ways ----
451 // to get to the CALLSEQ_BEGIN, but we need to find the path with the ----
452 // most nesting in order to ensure that we find the corresponding match. ----
453 if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::TokenFactor) { 0
454 for (const SDValue &Op : N->op_values()) 0
455 if (IsChainDependent(Op.getNode(), Inner, NestLevel, TII)) 0
456 return true; 0
457 return false; 0
458 } ----
459 // Check for a lowered CALLSEQ_BEGIN or CALLSEQ_END. ----
460 if (N->isMachineOpcode()) { 0
461 if (N->getMachineOpcode() == TII->getCallFrameDestroyOpcode()) { 0
462 ++NestLevel; 0
463 } else if (N->getMachineOpcode() == TII->getCallFrameSetupOpcode()) { 0
464 if (NestLevel == 0) 0
465 return false; 0
466 --NestLevel; 0
467 } ----
468 } ----
469 // Otherwise, find the chain and continue climbing. ----
470 for (const SDValue &Op : N->op_values()) 0
471 if (Op.getValueType() == MVT::Other) { 0
472 N = Op.getNode(); 0
473 goto found_chain_operand; 0
474 } ----
475 return false; 0
476 found_chain_operand:; 0
477 if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::EntryToken) 0
478 return false; 0
479 } 0
480 } ----
481 ----
482 /// FindCallSeqStart - Starting from the (lowered) CALLSEQ_END node, locate ----
483 /// the corresponding (lowered) CALLSEQ_BEGIN node. ----
484 /// ----
485 /// NestLevel and MaxNested are used in recursion to indcate the current level ----
486 /// of nesting of CALLSEQ_BEGIN and CALLSEQ_END pairs, as well as the maximum ----
487 /// level seen so far. ----
488 /// ----
489 /// TODO: It would be better to give CALLSEQ_END an explicit operand to point ----
490 /// to the corresponding CALLSEQ_BEGIN to avoid needing to search for it. ----
491 static SDNode * ----
492 FindCallSeqStart(SDNode *N, unsigned &NestLevel, unsigned &MaxNest, 0
493 const TargetInstrInfo *TII) { ----
494 while (true) { ----
495 // For a TokenFactor, examine each operand. There may be multiple ways ----
496 // to get to the CALLSEQ_BEGIN, but we need to find the path with the ----
497 // most nesting in order to ensure that we find the corresponding match. ----
498 if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::TokenFactor) { 0
499 SDNode *Best = nullptr; 0
500 unsigned BestMaxNest = MaxNest; 0
501 for (const SDValue &Op : N->op_values()) { 0
502 unsigned MyNestLevel = NestLevel; 0
503 unsigned MyMaxNest = MaxNest; 0
504 if (SDNode *New = FindCallSeqStart(Op.getNode(), 0
505 MyNestLevel, MyMaxNest, TII)) ----
506 if (!Best || (MyMaxNest > BestMaxNest)) { 0
507 Best = New; 0
508 BestMaxNest = MyMaxNest; 0
509 } ----
510 } ----
511 assert(Best); 0
512 MaxNest = BestMaxNest; 0
513 return Best; 0
514 } ----
515 // Check for a lowered CALLSEQ_BEGIN or CALLSEQ_END. ----
516 if (N->isMachineOpcode()) { 0
517 if (N->getMachineOpcode() == TII->getCallFrameDestroyOpcode()) { 0
518 ++NestLevel; 0
519 MaxNest = std::max(MaxNest, NestLevel); 0
520 } else if (N->getMachineOpcode() == TII->getCallFrameSetupOpcode()) { 0
521 assert(NestLevel != 0); 0
522 --NestLevel; 0
523 if (NestLevel == 0) 0
524 return N; 0
525 } ----
526 } ----
527 // Otherwise, find the chain and continue climbing. ----
528 for (const SDValue &Op : N->op_values()) 0

540 /// Call ReleasePred for each predecessor, then update register live def/gen. ----
541 /// Always update LiveRegDefs for a register dependence even if the current SU ----
542 /// also defines the register. This effectively create one large live range ----
543 /// across a sequence of two-address node. This is important because the ----
544 /// entire chain must be scheduled together. Example: ----
545 /// ----
546 /// flags = (3) add ----
547 /// flags = (2) addc flags ----
548 /// flags = (1) addc flags ----
549 /// ----
550 /// results in ----
551 /// ----
552 /// LiveRegDefs[flags] = 3 ----
553 /// LiveRegGens[flags] = 1 ----
554 /// ----
555 /// If (2) addc is unscheduled, then (1) addc must also be unscheduled to avoid ----
556 /// interference on flags. ----

558 // Bottom up: release predecessors ----
559 for (SDep &Pred : SU->Preds) { 76 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll

562 // This is a physical register dependency and it's impossible or ----
563 // expensive to copy the register. Make sure nothing that can ----
564 // clobber the register is scheduled between the predecessor and ----
565 // this node. ----
566 SUnit *RegDef = LiveRegDefs[Pred.getReg()]; (void)RegDef; 0
567 assert((!RegDef || RegDef == SU || RegDef == Pred.getSUnit()) && 0

570 if (!LiveRegGens[Pred.getReg()]) { 0

573 } ----
574 } ----
575 } ----

579 // these nodes, to prevent other calls from being interscheduled with them. ----

582 for (SDNode *Node = SU->getNode(); Node; Node = Node->getGluedNode()) 78 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
583 if (Node->isMachineOpcode() && 66 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
584 Node->getMachineOpcode() == TII->getCallFrameDestroyOpcode()) { 30 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
585 unsigned NestLevel = 0; 0
586 unsigned MaxNest = 0; 0

588 assert(N && "Must find call sequence start"); 0

836 /// UnscheduleNodeBottomUp - Remove the node from the schedule, update its and ----
837 /// its predecessor states to reflect the change. ----
838 void ScheduleDAGRRList::UnscheduleNodeBottomUp(SUnit *SU) { 0

840 LLVM_DEBUG(dumpNode(*SU)); 0
841 ----
842 for (SDep &Pred : SU->Preds) { 0

870 } ----
871 ----

873 // of a call. ----

928 /// After backtracking, the hazard checker needs to be restored to a state ----
929 /// corresponding the current cycle. ----
930 void ScheduleDAGRRList::RestoreHazardCheckerBottomUp() { 0

982 /// TryUnfold - Attempt to unfold ----
983 SUnit *ScheduleDAGRRList::TryUnfoldSU(SUnit *SU) { 0
984 SDNode *N = SU->getNode(); 0
985 // Use while over if to ease fall through. ----
986 SmallVector NewNodes; 0
987 if (!TII->unfoldMemoryOperand(*DAG, N, NewNodes)) 0
988 return nullptr; 0
989 ----
990 // unfolding an x86 DEC64m operation results in store, dec, load which ----
991 // can't be handled here so quit ----
992 if (NewNodes.size() == 3) 0
993 return nullptr; 0
994 ----
995 assert(NewNodes.size() == 2 && "Expected a load folding node!"); 0
996 ----
997 N = NewNodes[1]; 0
998 SDNode *LoadNode = NewNodes[0]; 0
999 unsigned NumVals = N->getNumValues(); 0
1000 unsigned OldNumVals = SU->getNode()->getNumValues(); 0
1001 ----
1002 // LoadNode may already exist. This can happen when there is another ----
1003 // load from the same location and producing the same type of value ----
1004 // but it has different alignment or volatileness. ----
1005 bool isNewLoad = true; 0
1006 SUnit *LoadSU; ----
1007 if (LoadNode->getNodeId() != -1) { 0
1008 LoadSU = &SUnits[LoadNode->getNodeId()]; 0
1009 // If LoadSU has already been scheduled, we should clone it but ----
1010 // this would negate the benefit to unfolding so just return SU. ----
1011 if (LoadSU->isScheduled) 0
1012 return SU; 0
1013 isNewLoad = false; 0
1014 } else { ----
1015 LoadSU = CreateNewSUnit(LoadNode); 0
1016 LoadNode->setNodeId(LoadSU->NodeNum); 0
1017 ----
1018 InitNumRegDefsLeft(LoadSU); 0
1019 computeLatency(LoadSU); 0
1020 } ----
1021 ----
1022 bool isNewN = true; 0
1023 SUnit *NewSU; ----
1024 // This can only happen when isNewLoad is false. ----
1025 if (N->getNodeId() != -1) { 0
1026 NewSU = &SUnits[N->getNodeId()]; 0
1027 // If NewSU has already been scheduled, we need to clone it, but this ----
1028 // negates the benefit to unfolding so just return SU. ----
1029 if (NewSU->isScheduled) { 0
1030 return SU; 0
1031 } ----
1032 isNewN = false; 0
1033 } else { ----
1034 NewSU = CreateNewSUnit(N); 0
1035 N->setNodeId(NewSU->NodeNum); 0
1036 ----
1037 const MCInstrDesc &MCID = TII->get(N->getMachineOpcode()); 0
1038 for (unsigned i = 0; i != MCID.getNumOperands(); ++i) { 0
1039 if (MCID.getOperandConstraint(i, MCOI::TIED_TO) != -1) { 0
1040 NewSU->isTwoAddress = true; 0
1041 break; 0
1042 } ----
1043 } ----
1044 if (MCID.isCommutable()) 0
1045 NewSU->isCommutable = true; 0
1046 ----
1047 InitNumRegDefsLeft(NewSU); 0
1048 computeLatency(NewSU); 0
1049 } ----
1050 ----
1051 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Unfolding SU #" << SU->NodeNum << "\n"); 0
1052 ----
1053 // Now that we are committed to unfolding replace DAG Uses. ----
1054 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumVals; ++i) 0
1055 DAG->ReplaceAllUsesOfValueWith(SDValue(SU->getNode(), i), SDValue(N, i)); 0
1056 DAG->ReplaceAllUsesOfValueWith(SDValue(SU->getNode(), OldNumVals - 1), 0
1057 SDValue(LoadNode, 1)); ----
1058 ----
1059 // Record all the edges to and from the old SU, by category. ----
1060 SmallVector ChainPreds; 0
1061 SmallVector ChainSuccs; 0
1062 SmallVector LoadPreds; 0
1063 SmallVector NodePreds; 0
1064 SmallVector NodeSuccs; 0
1065 for (SDep &Pred : SU->Preds) { 0
1066 if (Pred.isCtrl()) 0
1067 ChainPreds.push_back(Pred); 0
1068 else if (isOperandOf(Pred.getSUnit(), LoadNode)) 0
1069 LoadPreds.push_back(Pred); 0
1070 else ----
1071 NodePreds.push_back(Pred); 0
1072 } ----
1073 for (SDep &Succ : SU->Succs) { 0
1074 if (Succ.isCtrl()) 0
1075 ChainSuccs.push_back(Succ); 0
1076 else ----
1077 NodeSuccs.push_back(Succ); 0
1078 } ----
1079 ----
1080 // Now assign edges to the newly-created nodes. ----
1081 for (const SDep &Pred : ChainPreds) { 0
1082 RemovePred(SU, Pred); 0
1083 if (isNewLoad) 0
1084 AddPredQueued(LoadSU, Pred); 0
1085 } ----
1086 for (const SDep &Pred : LoadPreds) { 0
1087 RemovePred(SU, Pred); 0
1088 if (isNewLoad) 0
1089 AddPredQueued(LoadSU, Pred); 0
1090 } ----
1091 for (const SDep &Pred : NodePreds) { 0
1092 RemovePred(SU, Pred); 0
1093 AddPredQueued(NewSU, Pred); 0
1094 } ----
1095 for (SDep &D : NodeSuccs) { 0
1096 SUnit *SuccDep = D.getSUnit(); 0
1097 D.setSUnit(SU); 0
1098 RemovePred(SuccDep, D); 0
1099 D.setSUnit(NewSU); 0
1100 AddPredQueued(SuccDep, D); 0
1101 // Balance register pressure. ----
1102 if (AvailableQueue->tracksRegPressure() && SuccDep->isScheduled && 0
1103 !D.isCtrl() && NewSU->NumRegDefsLeft > 0) 0
1104 --NewSU->NumRegDefsLeft; 0
1105 } ----
1106 for (SDep &D : ChainSuccs) { 0
1107 SUnit *SuccDep = D.getSUnit(); 0
1108 D.setSUnit(SU); 0
1109 RemovePred(SuccDep, D); 0
1110 if (isNewLoad) { 0
1111 D.setSUnit(LoadSU); 0
1112 AddPredQueued(SuccDep, D); 0
1113 } ----
1114 } ----
1115 ----
1116 // Add a data dependency to reflect that NewSU reads the value defined ----
1117 // by LoadSU. ----
1118 SDep D(LoadSU, SDep::Data, 0); 0
1119 D.setLatency(LoadSU->Latency); 0
1120 AddPredQueued(NewSU, D); 0
1121 ----
1122 if (isNewLoad) 0
1123 AvailableQueue->addNode(LoadSU); 0
1124 if (isNewN) 0
1125 AvailableQueue->addNode(NewSU); 0
1126 ----
1127 ++NumUnfolds; 0
1128 ----
1129 if (NewSU->NumSuccsLeft == 0) 0
1130 NewSU->isAvailable = true; 0
1131 ----
1132 return NewSU; 0
1133 } 0

1135 /// CopyAndMoveSuccessors - Clone the specified node and move its scheduled ----
1136 /// successors to the newly created node. ----
1137 SUnit *ScheduleDAGRRList::CopyAndMoveSuccessors(SUnit *SU) { 0
1138 SDNode *N = SU->getNode(); 0
1139 if (!N) 0
1140 return nullptr; 0
1141 ----
1142 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Considering duplicating the SU\n"); 0
1143 LLVM_DEBUG(dumpNode(*SU)); 0
1144 ----
1145 if (N->getGluedNode() && 0
1146 !TII->canCopyGluedNodeDuringSchedule(N)) { 0
1147 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
1148 dbgs() ----
1149 << "Giving up because it has incoming glue and the target does not " ----
1150 "want to copy it\n"); ----

1152 } ----
1153 ----
1154 SUnit *NewSU; ----
1155 bool TryUnfold = false; 0
1156 for (unsigned i = 0, e = N->getNumValues(); i != e; ++i) { 0
1157 MVT VT = N->getSimpleValueType(i); 0
1158 if (VT == MVT::Glue) { 0
1159 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Giving up because it has outgoing glue\n"); 0
1160 return nullptr; 0
1161 } else if (VT == MVT::Other) 0
1162 TryUnfold = true; 0

1164 for (const SDValue &Op : N->op_values()) { 0

1167 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
1168 dbgs() << "Giving up because it one of the operands is glue and " ----
1169 "the target does not want to copy it\n"); ----
1170 return nullptr; 0
1171 } ----
1172 } ----
1173 ----
1174 // If possible unfold instruction. ----
1175 if (TryUnfold) { 0
1176 SUnit *UnfoldSU = TryUnfoldSU(SU); 0
1177 if (!UnfoldSU) 0
1178 return nullptr; 0
1179 SU = UnfoldSU; 0
1180 N = SU->getNode(); 0
1181 // If this can be scheduled don't bother duplicating and just return ----
1182 if (SU->NumSuccsLeft == 0) 0
1183 return SU; 0
1184 } ----
1185 ----
1186 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Duplicating SU #" << SU->NodeNum << "\n"); 0
1187 NewSU = CreateClone(SU); 0
1188 ----
1189 // New SUnit has the exact same predecessors. ----
1190 for (SDep &Pred : SU->Preds) 0
1191 if (!Pred.isArtificial()) 0
1192 AddPredQueued(NewSU, Pred); 0
1193 ----
1194 // Make sure the clone comes after the original. (InstrEmitter assumes ----
1195 // this ordering.) ----
1196 AddPredQueued(NewSU, SDep(SU, SDep::Artificial)); 0
1197 ----
1198 // Only copy scheduled successors. Cut them from old node's successor ----
1199 // list and move them over. ----
1200 SmallVector, 4> DelDeps; 0
1201 for (SDep &Succ : SU->Succs) { 0
1202 if (Succ.isArtificial()) 0
1203 continue; 0
1204 SUnit *SuccSU = Succ.getSUnit(); 0
1205 if (SuccSU->isScheduled) { 0
1206 SDep D = Succ; 0
1207 D.setSUnit(NewSU); 0
1208 AddPredQueued(SuccSU, D); 0
1209 D.setSUnit(SU); 0
1210 DelDeps.emplace_back(SuccSU, D); 0
1211 } ----
1212 } ----
1213 for (const auto &[DelSU, DelD] : DelDeps) 0
1214 RemovePred(DelSU, DelD); 0
1215 ----
1216 AvailableQueue->updateNode(SU); 0
1217 AvailableQueue->addNode(NewSU); 0
1218 ----

1223 /// InsertCopiesAndMoveSuccs - Insert register copies and move all ----
1224 /// scheduled successors of the given SUnit to the last copy. ----
1225 void ScheduleDAGRRList::InsertCopiesAndMoveSuccs(SUnit *SU, unsigned Reg, 0
1226 const TargetRegisterClass *DestRC, ----
1227 const TargetRegisterClass *SrcRC, ----
1228 SmallVectorImpl &Copies) { ----
1229 SUnit *CopyFromSU = CreateNewSUnit(nullptr); 0
1230 CopyFromSU->CopySrcRC = SrcRC; 0
1231 CopyFromSU->CopyDstRC = DestRC; 0
1232 ----
1233 SUnit *CopyToSU = CreateNewSUnit(nullptr); 0
1234 CopyToSU->CopySrcRC = DestRC; 0
1235 CopyToSU->CopyDstRC = SrcRC; 0
1236 ----
1237 // Only copy scheduled successors. Cut them from old node's successor ----
1238 // list and move them over. ----
1239 SmallVector, 4> DelDeps; 0
1240 for (SDep &Succ : SU->Succs) { 0
1241 if (Succ.isArtificial()) 0

1246 D.setSUnit(CopyToSU); 0
1247 AddPredQueued(SuccSU, D); 0

1252 // we could introduce another physreg interference on the copy and ----
1253 // continue inserting copies indefinitely. ----
1254 AddPredQueued(SuccSU, SDep(CopyFromSU, SDep::Artificial)); 0
1255 } ----
1256 } ----

1258 RemovePred(DelSU, DelD); 0

1260 SDep FromDep(SU, SDep::Data, Reg); 0
1261 FromDep.setLatency(SU->Latency); 0
1262 AddPredQueued(CopyFromSU, FromDep); 0
1263 SDep ToDep(CopyFromSU, SDep::Data, 0); 0
1264 ToDep.setLatency(CopyFromSU->Latency); 0
1265 AddPredQueued(CopyToSU, ToDep); 0
1266 ----
1267 AvailableQueue->updateNode(SU); 0
1268 AvailableQueue->addNode(CopyFromSU); 0
1269 AvailableQueue->addNode(CopyToSU); 0
1270 Copies.push_back(CopyFromSU); 0
1271 Copies.push_back(CopyToSU); 0
1272 ----
1273 ++NumPRCopies; 0
1274 } 0

1299 /// CheckForLiveRegDef - Return true and update live register vector if the ----
1300 /// specified register def of the specified SUnit clobbers any "live" registers. ----
1301 static void CheckForLiveRegDef(SUnit *SU, unsigned Reg, SUnit **LiveRegDefs, 0
1302 SmallSet &RegAdded, ----
1303 SmallVectorImpl &LRegs, ----
1304 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI, ----
1305 const SDNode *Node = nullptr) { ----
1306 for (MCRegAliasIterator AliasI(Reg, TRI, true); AliasI.isValid(); ++AliasI) { 0
1307 ----
1308 // Check if Ref is live. ----
1309 if (!LiveRegDefs[*AliasI]) continue; 0
1310 ----
1311 // Allow multiple uses of the same def. ----
1312 if (LiveRegDefs[*AliasI] == SU) continue; 0
1313 ----
1314 // Allow multiple uses of same def ----
1315 if (Node && LiveRegDefs[*AliasI]->getNode() == Node) 0
1316 continue; 0
1317 ----
1318 // Add Reg to the set of interfering live regs. ----
1319 if (RegAdded.insert(*AliasI).second) { 0
1320 LRegs.push_back(*AliasI); 0
1321 } ----
1322 } ----
1323 } 0

1325 /// CheckForLiveRegDefMasked - Check for any live physregs that are clobbered ----
1326 /// by RegMask, and add them to LRegs. ----
1327 static void CheckForLiveRegDefMasked(SUnit *SU, const uint32_t *RegMask, 0
1328 ArrayRef LiveRegDefs, ----
1329 SmallSet &RegAdded, ----
1330 SmallVectorImpl &LRegs) { ----
1331 // Look at all live registers. Skip Reg0 and the special CallResource. ----
1332 for (unsigned i = 1, e = LiveRegDefs.size()-1; i != e; ++i) { 0
1333 if (!LiveRegDefs[i]) continue; 0
1334 if (LiveRegDefs[i] == SU) continue; 0
1335 if (!MachineOperand::clobbersPhysReg(RegMask, i)) continue; 0
1336 if (RegAdded.insert(i).second) 0
1337 LRegs.push_back(i); 0
1338 } ----
1339 } 0

1450 // Add the nodes that aren't ready back onto the available list. ----
1451 for (unsigned i = Interferences.size(); i > 0; --i) { 0

1506 // We query the topological order in the loop body, so make sure outstanding ----
1507 // updates are applied before entering it (we only enter the loop if there ----
1508 // are some interferences). If we make changes to the ordering, we exit ----
1509 // the loop. ----
1510 ----
1511 // All candidates are delayed due to live physical reg dependencies. ----
1512 // Try backtracking, code duplication, or inserting cross class copies ----
1513 // to resolve it. ----
1514 for (SUnit *TrySU : Interferences) { 0
1515 SmallVectorImpl &LRegs = LRegsMap[TrySU]; 0
1516 ----
1517 // Try unscheduling up to the point where it's safe to schedule ----
1518 // this node. ----
1519 SUnit *BtSU = nullptr; 0
1520 unsigned LiveCycle = std::numeric_limits::max(); 0
1521 for (unsigned Reg : LRegs) { 0
1522 if (LiveRegGens[Reg]->getHeight() < LiveCycle) { 0
1523 BtSU = LiveRegGens[Reg]; 0
1524 LiveCycle = BtSU->getHeight(); 0
1525 } ----
1526 } ----
1527 if (!WillCreateCycle(TrySU, BtSU)) { 0
1528 // BacktrackBottomUp mutates Interferences! ----
1529 BacktrackBottomUp(TrySU, BtSU); 0

1532 // requires the physical reg dep. ----
1533 if (BtSU->isAvailable) { 0

1535 if (!BtSU->isPending) 0
1536 AvailableQueue->remove(BtSU); 0
1537 } ----
1538 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ARTIFICIAL edge from SU(" << BtSU->NodeNum 0
1539 << ") to SU(" << TrySU->NodeNum << ")\n"); ----
1540 AddPredQueued(TrySU, SDep(BtSU, SDep::Artificial)); 0
1541 ----
1542 // If one or more successors has been unscheduled, then the current ----
1543 // node is no longer available. ----
1544 if (!TrySU->isAvailable || !TrySU->NodeQueueId) { 0
1545 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "TrySU not available; choosing node from queue\n"); 0
1546 CurSU = AvailableQueue->pop(); 0
1547 } else { ----
1548 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "TrySU available\n"); 0
1549 // Available and in AvailableQueue ----
1550 AvailableQueue->remove(TrySU); 0
1551 CurSU = TrySU; 0
1552 } ----
1553 FindAvailableNode(); 0
1554 // Interferences has been mutated. We must break. ----
1555 break; 0
1556 } ----
1557 } ----
1558 ----
1559 if (!CurSU) { 0
1560 // Can't backtrack. If it's too expensive to copy the value, then try ----
1561 // duplicate the nodes that produces these "too expensive to copy" ----
1562 // values to break the dependency. In case even that doesn't work, ----
1563 // insert cross class copies. ----
1564 // If it's not too expensive, i.e. cost != -1, issue copies. ----
1565 SUnit *TrySU = Interferences[0]; 0
1566 SmallVectorImpl &LRegs = LRegsMap[TrySU]; 0
1567 assert(LRegs.size() == 1 && "Can't handle this yet!"); 0

1574 ----
1575 // If cross copy register class is the same as RC, then it must be possible ----
1576 // copy the value directly. Do not try duplicate the def. ----
1577 // If cross copy register class is not the same as RC, then it's possible to ----
1578 // copy the value but it require cross register class copies and it is ----
1579 // expensive. ----
1580 // If cross copy register class is null, then it's not possible to copy ----
1581 // the value at all. ----
1582 SUnit *NewDef = nullptr; 0
1583 if (DestRC != RC) { 0
1584 NewDef = CopyAndMoveSuccessors(LRDef); 0
1585 if (!DestRC && !NewDef) 0

1596 } 0
1597 ----
1598 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Adding an edge from SU #" << NewDef->NodeNum 0
1599 << " to SU #" << TrySU->NodeNum << "\n"); ----

1601 AddPredQueued(NewDef, SDep(TrySU, SDep::Artificial)); 0

2202 if (PredSU->NumRegDefsLeft == 0) { 0

2204 } ----
2205 // FIXME: The ScheduleDAG currently loses information about which of a ----

2208 // here. Instead the following loop consumes the register defs in an ----

2213 // value type or register class to SDep. ----

2224 if (SkipRegDefs) 0
2225 continue; 0
2226 ----
2227 unsigned RCId, Cost; ----
2228 GetCostForDef(RegDefPos, TLI, TII, TRI, RCId, Cost, MF); 0
2229 RegPressure[RCId] += Cost; 0
2230 break; 0

2232 } ----

2242 unsigned RCId, Cost; ----

2441 ----
2442 SU->isVRegCycle = true; 0
2443 ----
2444 for (const SDep &Pred : SU->Preds) { 0
2445 if (Pred.isCtrl()) continue; 0
2446 Pred.getSUnit()->isVRegCycle = true; 0
2447 } ----
2448 } ----

2485 // Check for either a dependence (latency) or resource (hazard) stall. ----

2488 static bool BUHasStall(SUnit *SU, int Height, RegReductionPQBase *SPQ) { 0

2496 // Return -1 if left has higher priority, 1 if right has higher priority. ----
2497 // Return 0 if latency-based priority is equivalent. ----
2498 static int BUCompareLatency(SUnit *left, SUnit *right, bool checkPref, 0
2499 RegReductionPQBase *SPQ) { ----
2500 // Scheduling an instruction that uses a VReg whose postincrement has not yet ----
2501 // been scheduled will induce a copy. Model this as an extra cycle of latency. ----
2502 int LPenalty = hasVRegCycleUse(left) ? 1 : 0; 0
2503 int RPenalty = hasVRegCycleUse(right) ? 1 : 0; 0
2504 int LHeight = (int)left->getHeight() + LPenalty; 0
2505 int RHeight = (int)right->getHeight() + RPenalty; 0
2506 ----
2507 bool LStall = (!checkPref || left->SchedulingPref == Sched::ILP) && 0
2508 BUHasStall(left, LHeight, SPQ); 0
2509 bool RStall = (!checkPref || right->SchedulingPref == Sched::ILP) && 0
2510 BUHasStall(right, RHeight, SPQ); 0
2511 ----
2512 // If scheduling one of the node will cause a pipeline stall, delay it. ----
2513 // If scheduling either one of the node will cause a pipeline stall, sort ----
2514 // them according to their height. ----
2515 if (LStall) { 0
2516 if (!RStall) 0
2517 return 1; 0
2518 if (LHeight != RHeight) 0
2519 return LHeight > RHeight ? 1 : -1; 0
2520 } else if (RStall) 0
2521 return -1; 0
2522 ----
2523 // If either node is scheduling for latency, sort them by height/depth ----
2524 // and latency. ----
2525 if (!checkPref || (left->SchedulingPref == Sched::ILP || 0
2526 right->SchedulingPref == Sched::ILP)) { 0
2527 // If neither instruction stalls (!LStall && !RStall) and HazardRecognizer ----
2528 // is enabled, grouping instructions by cycle, then its height is already ----
2529 // covered so only its depth matters. We also reach this point if both stall ----
2530 // but have the same height. ----
2531 if (!SPQ->getHazardRec()->isEnabled()) { 0
2532 if (LHeight != RHeight) 0
2533 return LHeight > RHeight ? 1 : -1; 0
2534 } ----
2535 int LDepth = left->getDepth() - LPenalty; 0
2536 int RDepth = right->getDepth() - RPenalty; 0
2537 if (LDepth != RDepth) { 0
2538 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Comparing latency of SU (" << left->NodeNum 0
2539 << ") depth " << LDepth << " vs SU (" << right->NodeNum ----
2540 << ") depth " << RDepth << "\n"); ----
2541 return LDepth < RDepth ? 1 : -1; 0
2542 } ----
2543 if (left->Latency != right->Latency) 0
2544 return left->Latency > right->Latency ? 1 : -1; 0
2545 } ----
2546 return 0; 0
2547 } ----

2549 static bool BURRSort(SUnit *left, SUnit *right, RegReductionPQBase *SPQ) { 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2550 // Schedule physical register definitions close to their use. This is ----
2551 // motivated by microarchitectures that can fuse cmp+jump macro-ops. But as ----
2552 // long as shortening physreg live ranges is generally good, we can defer ----
2553 // creating a subtarget hook. ----
2554 if (!DisableSchedPhysRegJoin) { 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2555 bool LHasPhysReg = left->hasPhysRegDefs; 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2556 bool RHasPhysReg = right->hasPhysRegDefs; 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2557 if (LHasPhysReg != RHasPhysReg) { 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2558 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
2559 static const char *const PhysRegMsg[] = { " has no physreg", ----
2560 " defines a physreg" }; ----
2561 #endif ----
2562 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " SU (" << left->NodeNum << ") " 0
2563 << PhysRegMsg[LHasPhysReg] << " SU(" << right->NodeNum ----
2564 << ") " << PhysRegMsg[RHasPhysReg] << "\n"); ----
2565 return LHasPhysReg < RHasPhysReg; 0
2566 } ----
2567 } ----
2568 ----
2569 // Prioritize by Sethi-Ulmann number and push CopyToReg nodes down. ----
2570 unsigned LPriority = SPQ->getNodePriority(left); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2571 unsigned RPriority = SPQ->getNodePriority(right); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2572 ----
2573 // Be really careful about hoisting call operands above previous calls. ----
2574 // Only allows it if it would reduce register pressure. ----
2575 if (left->isCall && right->isCallOp) { 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2576 unsigned RNumVals = right->getNode()->getNumValues(); 0
2577 RPriority = (RPriority > RNumVals) ? (RPriority - RNumVals) : 0; 0
2578 } ----
2579 if (right->isCall && left->isCallOp) { 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2580 unsigned LNumVals = left->getNode()->getNumValues(); 0
2581 LPriority = (LPriority > LNumVals) ? (LPriority - LNumVals) : 0; 0
2582 } ----
2583 ----
2584 if (LPriority != RPriority) 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2585 return LPriority > RPriority; 0
2586 ----
2587 // One or both of the nodes are calls and their sethi-ullman numbers are the ----
2588 // same, then keep source order. ----
2589 if (left->isCall || right->isCall) { 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2590 unsigned LOrder = SPQ->getNodeOrdering(left); 0
2591 unsigned ROrder = SPQ->getNodeOrdering(right); 0
2592 ----
2593 // Prefer an ordering where the lower the non-zero order number, the higher ----
2594 // the preference. ----
2595 if ((LOrder || ROrder) && LOrder != ROrder) 0
2596 return LOrder != 0 && (LOrder < ROrder || ROrder == 0); 0
2597 } ----
2598 ----
2599 // Try schedule def + use closer when Sethi-Ullman numbers are the same. ----
2600 // e.g. ----
2601 // t1 = op t2, c1 ----
2602 // t3 = op t4, c2 ----
2603 // ----
2604 // and the following instructions are both ready. ----
2605 // t2 = op c3 ----
2606 // t4 = op c4 ----
2607 // ----
2608 // Then schedule t2 = op first. ----
2609 // i.e. ----
2610 // t4 = op c4 ----
2611 // t2 = op c3 ----
2612 // t1 = op t2, c1 ----
2613 // t3 = op t4, c2 ----
2614 // ----
2615 // This creates more short live intervals. ----
2616 unsigned LDist = closestSucc(left); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2617 unsigned RDist = closestSucc(right); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2618 if (LDist != RDist) 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2619 return LDist < RDist; 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2620 ----
2621 // How many registers becomes live when the node is scheduled. ----
2622 unsigned LScratch = calcMaxScratches(left); 0
2623 unsigned RScratch = calcMaxScratches(right); 0
2624 if (LScratch != RScratch) 0
2625 return LScratch > RScratch; 0
2626 ----
2627 // Comparing latency against a call makes little sense unless the node ----
2628 // is register pressure-neutral. ----
2629 if ((left->isCall && RPriority > 0) || (right->isCall && LPriority > 0)) 0
2630 return (left->NodeQueueId > right->NodeQueueId); 0
2631 ----
2632 // Do not compare latencies when one or both of the nodes are calls. ----
2633 if (!DisableSchedCycles && 0
2634 !(left->isCall || right->isCall)) { 0
2635 int result = BUCompareLatency(left, right, false /*checkPref*/, SPQ); 0
2636 if (result != 0) 0
2637 return result > 0; 0
2638 } ----
2639 else { ----
2640 if (left->getHeight() != right->getHeight()) 0
2641 return left->getHeight() > right->getHeight(); 0
2642 ----
2643 if (left->getDepth() != right->getDepth()) 0
2644 return left->getDepth() < right->getDepth(); 0
2645 } ----
2646 ----
2647 assert(left->NodeQueueId && right->NodeQueueId && 0
2648 "NodeQueueId cannot be zero"); ----
2649 return (left->NodeQueueId > right->NodeQueueId); 0

2694 // Return true if right should be scheduled with higher priority than left. ----
2695 bool hybrid_ls_rr_sort::operator()(SUnit *left, SUnit *right) const { 0
2696 if (int res = checkSpecialNodes(left, right)) 0
2697 return res > 0; 0
2698 ----
2699 if (left->isCall || right->isCall) 0
2700 // No way to compute latency of calls. ----
2701 return BURRSort(left, right, SPQ); 0
2702 ----
2703 bool LHigh = SPQ->HighRegPressure(left); 0
2704 bool RHigh = SPQ->HighRegPressure(right); 0
2705 // Avoid causing spills. If register pressure is high, schedule for ----
2706 // register pressure reduction. ----
2707 if (LHigh && !RHigh) { 0
2708 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " pressure SU(" << left->NodeNum << ") > SU(" 0
2709 << right->NodeNum << ")\n"); ----
2710 return true; 0
2711 } ----
2712 else if (!LHigh && RHigh) { 0
2713 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " pressure SU(" << right->NodeNum << ") > SU(" 0
2714 << left->NodeNum << ")\n"); ----
2715 return false; 0
2716 } ----
2717 if (!LHigh && !RHigh) { 0
2718 int result = BUCompareLatency(left, right, true /*checkPref*/, SPQ); 0
2719 if (result != 0) 0
2720 return result > 0; 0
2721 } ----
2722 return BURRSort(left, right, SPQ); 0
2723 } ----

2737 static bool canEnableCoalescing(SUnit *SU) { 0
2738 unsigned Opc = SU->getNode() ? SU->getNode()->getOpcode() : 0; 0
2739 if (Opc == ISD::TokenFactor || Opc == ISD::CopyToReg) 0
2740 // CopyToReg should be close to its uses to facilitate coalescing and ----
2741 // avoid spilling. ----
2742 return true; 0
2743 ----
2744 if (Opc == TargetOpcode::EXTRACT_SUBREG || 0
2745 Opc == TargetOpcode::SUBREG_TO_REG || 0
2746 Opc == TargetOpcode::INSERT_SUBREG) ----
2747 // EXTRACT_SUBREG, INSERT_SUBREG, and SUBREG_TO_REG nodes should be ----
2748 // close to their uses to facilitate coalescing. ----
2749 return true; 0
2750 ----
2751 if (SU->NumPreds == 0 && SU->NumSuccs != 0) 0
2752 // If SU does not have a register def, schedule it close to its uses ----
2753 // because it does not lengthen any live ranges. ----
2754 return true; 0
2755 ----
2756 return false; 0
2757 } ----

2761 bool ilp_ls_rr_sort::operator()(SUnit *left, SUnit *right) const { 0
2762 if (int res = checkSpecialNodes(left, right)) 0
2763 return res > 0; 0
2764 ----
2765 if (left->isCall || right->isCall) 0
2766 // No way to compute latency of calls. ----
2767 return BURRSort(left, right, SPQ); 0
2768 ----
2769 unsigned LLiveUses = 0, RLiveUses = 0; 0
2770 int LPDiff = 0, RPDiff = 0; 0
2771 if (!DisableSchedRegPressure || !DisableSchedLiveUses) { 0
2772 LPDiff = SPQ->RegPressureDiff(left, LLiveUses); 0
2773 RPDiff = SPQ->RegPressureDiff(right, RLiveUses); 0
2774 } ----
2775 if (!DisableSchedRegPressure && LPDiff != RPDiff) { 0
2776 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "RegPressureDiff SU(" << left->NodeNum 0
2777 << "): " << LPDiff << " != SU(" << right->NodeNum ----
2778 << "): " << RPDiff << "\n"); ----
2779 return LPDiff > RPDiff; 0
2780 } ----
2781 ----
2782 if (!DisableSchedRegPressure && (LPDiff > 0 || RPDiff > 0)) { 0
2783 bool LReduce = canEnableCoalescing(left); 0
2784 bool RReduce = canEnableCoalescing(right); 0
2785 if (LReduce && !RReduce) return false; 0
2786 if (RReduce && !LReduce) return true; 0
2787 } ----
2788 ----
2789 if (!DisableSchedLiveUses && (LLiveUses != RLiveUses)) { 0
2790 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Live uses SU(" << left->NodeNum << "): " << LLiveUses 0
2791 << " != SU(" << right->NodeNum << "): " << RLiveUses ----
2792 << "\n"); ----
2793 return LLiveUses < RLiveUses; 0
2794 } ----
2795 ----
2796 if (!DisableSchedStalls) { 0
2797 bool LStall = BUHasStall(left, left->getHeight(), SPQ); 0
2798 bool RStall = BUHasStall(right, right->getHeight(), SPQ); 0
2799 if (LStall != RStall) 0
2800 return left->getHeight() > right->getHeight(); 0
2801 } ----
2802 ----
2803 if (!DisableSchedCriticalPath) { 0
2804 int spread = (int)left->getDepth() - (int)right->getDepth(); 0
2805 if (std::abs(spread) > MaxReorderWindow) { 0
2806 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Depth of SU(" << left->NodeNum << "): " 0
2807 << left->getDepth() << " != SU(" << right->NodeNum ----
2808 << "): " << right->getDepth() << "\n"); ----
2809 return left->getDepth() < right->getDepth(); 0
2810 } ----
2811 } ----
2812 ----
2813 if (!DisableSchedHeight && left->getHeight() != right->getHeight()) { 0
2814 int spread = (int)left->getHeight() - (int)right->getHeight(); 0
2815 if (std::abs(spread) > MaxReorderWindow) 0
2816 return left->getHeight() > right->getHeight(); 0
2817 } ----
2818 ----
2819 return BURRSort(left, right, SPQ); 0
2820 } ----

2861 /// canClobberReachingPhysRegUse - True if SU would clobber one of it's ----

2863 /// i.e. DepSU should not be scheduled above SU. ----
2864 static bool canClobberReachingPhysRegUse(const SUnit *DepSU, const SUnit *SU, 0

2934 /// PrescheduleNodesWithMultipleUses - Nodes with multiple uses ----
2935 /// are not handled well by the general register pressure reduction ----
2936 /// heuristics. When presented with code like this: ----
2937 /// ----
2938 /// N ----
2939 /// / | ----
2940 /// / | ----
2941 /// U store ----
2942 /// | ----
2943 /// ... ----
2944 /// ----
2945 /// the heuristics tend to push the store up, but since the ----
2946 /// operand of the store has another use (U), this would increase ----
2947 /// the length of that other use (the U->N edge). ----
2948 /// ----
2949 /// This function transforms code like the above to route U's ----
2950 /// dependence through the store when possible, like this: ----
2951 /// ----
2952 /// N ----
2953 /// || ----
2954 /// || ----
2955 /// store ----
2956 /// | ----
2957 /// U ----
2958 /// | ----
2959 /// ... ----
2960 /// ----
2961 /// This results in the store being scheduled immediately ----
2962 /// after N, which shortens the U->N live range, reducing ----
2963 /// register pressure. ----
2964 void RegReductionPQBase::PrescheduleNodesWithMultipleUses() { 0
2965 // Visit all the nodes in topological order, working top-down. ----
2966 for (SUnit &SU : *SUnits) { 0
2967 // For now, only look at nodes with no data successors, such as stores. ----
2968 // These are especially important, due to the heuristics in ----
2969 // getNodePriority for nodes with no data successors. ----
2970 if (SU.NumSuccs != 0) 0
2971 continue; 0
2972 // For now, only look at nodes with exactly one data predecessor. ----
2973 if (SU.NumPreds != 1) 0
2974 continue; 0
2975 // Avoid prescheduling copies to virtual registers, which don't behave ----
2976 // like other nodes from the perspective of scheduling heuristics. ----
2977 if (SDNode *N = SU.getNode()) 0
2978 if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::CopyToReg && 0
2979 cast(N->getOperand(1))->getReg().isVirtual()) 0
2980 continue; 0
2981 ----
2982 SDNode *PredFrameSetup = nullptr; 0
2983 for (const SDep &Pred : SU.Preds) 0
2984 if (Pred.isCtrl() && Pred.getSUnit()) { 0
2985 // Find the predecessor which is not data dependence. ----
2986 SDNode *PredND = Pred.getSUnit()->getNode(); 0
2987 ----
2988 // If PredND is FrameSetup, we should not pre-scheduled the node, ----
2989 // or else, when bottom up scheduling, ADJCALLSTACKDOWN and ----
2990 // ADJCALLSTACKUP may hold CallResource too long and make other ----
2991 // calls can't be scheduled. If there's no other available node ----
2992 // to schedule, the schedular will try to rename the register by ----
2993 // creating copy to avoid the conflict which will fail because ----
2994 // CallResource is not a real physical register. ----
2995 if (PredND && PredND->isMachineOpcode() && 0
2996 (PredND->getMachineOpcode() == TII->getCallFrameSetupOpcode())) { 0
2997 PredFrameSetup = PredND; 0
2998 break; 0
2999 } ----
3000 } ----
3001 // Skip the node has FrameSetup parent. ----
3002 if (PredFrameSetup != nullptr) 0
3003 continue; 0
3004 ----
3005 // Locate the single data predecessor. ----
3006 SUnit *PredSU = nullptr; 0
3007 for (const SDep &Pred : SU.Preds) 0
3008 if (!Pred.isCtrl()) { 0
3009 PredSU = Pred.getSUnit(); 0
3010 break; 0
3011 } ----
3012 assert(PredSU); 0
3013 ----
3014 // Don't rewrite edges that carry physregs, because that requires additional ----
3015 // support infrastructure. ----
3016 if (PredSU->hasPhysRegDefs) 0
3017 continue; 0
3018 // Short-circuit the case where SU is PredSU's only data successor. ----
3019 if (PredSU->NumSuccs == 1) 0
3020 continue; 0
3021 // Avoid prescheduling to copies from virtual registers, which don't behave ----
3022 // like other nodes from the perspective of scheduling heuristics. ----
3023 if (SDNode *N = SU.getNode()) 0
3024 if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::CopyFromReg && 0
3025 cast(N->getOperand(1))->getReg().isVirtual()) 0
3026 continue; 0
3027 ----
3028 // Perform checks on the successors of PredSU. ----
3029 for (const SDep &PredSucc : PredSU->Succs) { 0
3030 SUnit *PredSuccSU = PredSucc.getSUnit(); 0
3031 if (PredSuccSU == &SU) continue; 0
3032 // If PredSU has another successor with no data successors, for ----
3033 // now don't attempt to choose either over the other. ----
3034 if (PredSuccSU->NumSuccs == 0) 0
3035 goto outer_loop_continue; 0
3036 // Don't break physical register dependencies. ----
3037 if (SU.hasPhysRegClobbers && PredSuccSU->hasPhysRegDefs) 0
3038 if (canClobberPhysRegDefs(PredSuccSU, &SU, TII, TRI)) 0
3039 goto outer_loop_continue; 0
3040 // Don't introduce graph cycles. ----
3041 if (scheduleDAG->IsReachable(&SU, PredSuccSU)) 0
3042 goto outer_loop_continue; 0
3043 } ----
3044 ----
3045 // Ok, the transformation is safe and the heuristics suggest it is ----
3046 // profitable. Update the graph. ----
3047 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
3048 dbgs() << " Prescheduling SU #" << SU.NodeNum << " next to PredSU #" ----
3049 << PredSU->NodeNum ----
3050 << " to guide scheduling in the presence of multiple uses\n"); ----

3053 assert(!Edge.isAssignedRegDep()); 0

3055 if (SuccSU != &SU) { 0
3056 Edge.setSUnit(PredSU); 0
3057 scheduleDAG->RemovePred(SuccSU, Edge); 0
3058 scheduleDAG->AddPredQueued(&SU, Edge); 0
3059 Edge.setSUnit(&SU); 0
3060 scheduleDAG->AddPredQueued(SuccSU, Edge); 0
3061 --i; 0
3062 } ----
3063 } ----
3064 outer_loop_continue:; 0
3065 } ----
3066 } 0

3068 /// AddPseudoTwoAddrDeps - If two nodes share an operand and one of them uses ----
3069 /// it as a def&use operand. Add a pseudo control edge from it to the other ----
3070 /// node (if it won't create a cycle) so the two-address one will be scheduled ----
3071 /// first (lower in the schedule). If both nodes are two-address, favor the ----
3072 /// one that has a CopyToReg use (more likely to be a loop induction update). ----
3073 /// If both are two-address, but one is commutable while the other is not ----
3074 /// commutable, favor the one that's not commutable. ----
3075 void RegReductionPQBase::AddPseudoTwoAddrDeps() { 0
3076 for (SUnit &SU : *SUnits) { 0
3077 if (!SU.isTwoAddress) 0
3078 continue; 0
3079 ----
3080 SDNode *Node = SU.getNode(); 0
3081 if (!Node || !Node->isMachineOpcode() || SU.getNode()->getGluedNode()) 0
3082 continue; 0
3083 ----
3084 bool isLiveOut = hasOnlyLiveOutUses(&SU); 0
3085 unsigned Opc = Node->getMachineOpcode(); 0
3086 const MCInstrDesc &MCID = TII->get(Opc); 0
3087 unsigned NumRes = MCID.getNumDefs(); 0
3088 unsigned NumOps = MCID.getNumOperands() - NumRes; 0
3089 for (unsigned j = 0; j != NumOps; ++j) { 0
3090 if (MCID.getOperandConstraint(j+NumRes, MCOI::TIED_TO) == -1) 0
3091 continue; 0
3092 SDNode *DU = SU.getNode()->getOperand(j).getNode(); 0
3093 if (DU->getNodeId() == -1) 0
3094 continue; 0
3095 const SUnit *DUSU = &(*SUnits)[DU->getNodeId()]; 0
3096 if (!DUSU) 0
3097 continue; 0
3098 for (const SDep &Succ : DUSU->Succs) { 0
3099 if (Succ.isCtrl()) 0
3100 continue; 0
3101 SUnit *SuccSU = Succ.getSUnit(); 0
3102 if (SuccSU == &SU) 0
3103 continue; 0
3104 // Be conservative. Ignore if nodes aren't at roughly the same ----
3105 // depth and height. ----
3106 if (SuccSU->getHeight() < SU.getHeight() && 0
3107 (SU.getHeight() - SuccSU->getHeight()) > 1) 0
3108 continue; 0
3109 // Skip past COPY_TO_REGCLASS nodes, so that the pseudo edge ----
3110 // constrains whatever is using the copy, instead of the copy ----
3111 // itself. In the case that the copy is coalesced, this ----
3112 // preserves the intent of the pseudo two-address heurietics. ----
3113 while (SuccSU->Succs.size() == 1 && 0
3114 SuccSU->getNode()->isMachineOpcode() && 0
3115 SuccSU->getNode()->getMachineOpcode() == 0
3116 TargetOpcode::COPY_TO_REGCLASS) ----
3117 SuccSU = SuccSU->Succs.front().getSUnit(); 0
3118 // Don't constrain non-instruction nodes. ----
3119 if (!SuccSU->getNode() || !SuccSU->getNode()->isMachineOpcode()) 0
3120 continue; 0
3121 // Don't constrain nodes with physical register defs if the ----
3122 // predecessor can clobber them. ----
3123 if (SuccSU->hasPhysRegDefs && SU.hasPhysRegClobbers) { 0
3124 if (canClobberPhysRegDefs(SuccSU, &SU, TII, TRI)) 0
3125 continue; 0
3126 } ----
3127 // Don't constrain EXTRACT_SUBREG, INSERT_SUBREG, and SUBREG_TO_REG; ----
3128 // these may be coalesced away. We want them close to their uses. ----
3129 unsigned SuccOpc = SuccSU->getNode()->getMachineOpcode(); 0
3130 if (SuccOpc == TargetOpcode::EXTRACT_SUBREG || 0
3131 SuccOpc == TargetOpcode::INSERT_SUBREG || 0
3132 SuccOpc == TargetOpcode::SUBREG_TO_REG) ----
3133 continue; 0
3134 if (!canClobberReachingPhysRegUse(SuccSU, &SU, scheduleDAG, TII, TRI) && 0
3135 (!canClobber(SuccSU, DUSU) || 0
3136 (isLiveOut && !hasOnlyLiveOutUses(SuccSU)) || 0
3137 (!SU.isCommutable && SuccSU->isCommutable)) && 0
3138 !scheduleDAG->IsReachable(SuccSU, &SU)) { 0
3139 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() 0
3140 << " Adding a pseudo-two-addr edge from SU #" ----
3141 << SU.NodeNum << " to SU #" << SuccSU->NodeNum << "\n"); ----
3142 scheduleDAG->AddPredQueued(&SU, SDep(SuccSU, SDep::Artificial)); 0
3143 } ----
3144 } ----
3145 } ----
3146 } ----

9 // This implements bottom-up and top-down register pressure reduction list 9 // This implements bottom-up and top-down register pressure reduction list
10 // schedulers, using standard algorithms. The basic approach uses a priority 10 // schedulers, using standard algorithms. The basic approach uses a priority
11 // queue of available nodes to schedule. One at a time, nodes are taken from 11 // queue of available nodes to schedule. One at a time, nodes are taken from
12 // the priority queue (thus in priority order), checked for legality to 12 // the priority queue (thus in priority order), checked for legality to
13 // schedule, and emitted if legal. 13 // schedule, and emitted if legal.
